<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 08 at 11:32AM CST  by NWS Houston - Galveston</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHWESTERN TRINITY...
NORTHEASTERN GRIMES...NORTHWESTERN SAN JACINTO...SOUTH CENTRAL
HOUSTON...SOUTHEASTERN MADISON...WESTERN POLK AND WALKER COUNTIES
THROUGH NOON CST...
At 1131 AM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Huntsville, moving northeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Huntsville, Trinity, Lovelady, Riverside, Sebastopol, and Crabbs
Prairie.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
